    "These include depressive symptoms (PHQ-9, Kroenke et al., 2001), Satisfaction with life (SWLS, Diener et al., 1985) and emotion regulation quality (ERQ Gross & John, 2003)",
    "Comparing quality of reappraisals.",
    "Next, we compared the quality of reappraisals between humans and GPT using a linear mixed effect model.",
    "We conducted an interaction between source of reappraisal (human, GPT) and vignette emotion (sadness, anger, anxiety) while controlling for reappraisal length and the order in which each reappraisal was displayed to each rater.",
    "We further included three random intercepts to capture variance in ratings between raters, variance in base reappraisal ability between reappraisers, and lastly variance between individual vignettes."
